SIMPLE: centenary
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Centenary
<hw>Cen"te*na*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>centenarius</ets>, fr. <ets>centum</ets> a hundred.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Relating to, or consisting of, a hundred.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Occurring once in every hundred years;
centennial.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Centenary</xex> solemnities.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Fuller.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Centenary</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Centenary
<hw>Cen"te*na*ry</hw>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Centenaries</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
aggregate of a hundred single things; specifically, a century.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧Every <xex>centenary</xex> of years.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Hakewill.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A commemoration or celebration of an event which
occurred a hundred years before.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Centennial</ent>⟦br⟧
